# Audio Preprocessing Notebook

This notebook demonstrates audio preprocessing techniques.

## Setup

```python
import sys
from pathlib import Path
sys.path.insert(0, str(Path.cwd().parent))

from src.data.audio_loader import AudioLoader
from src.data.preprocessing import AudioPreprocessor
from src.utils.audio_utils import AudioUtils
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
```

## Load Audio

```python
loader = AudioLoader()
samples = loader.load_all_samples()

# Get first sample
category = list(samples.keys())[
    0
]
audio, filename = samples[category
][
    0
]
print(f"Original audio shape: {audio.shape}")
```

## Preprocessing

```python
preprocessor = AudioPreprocessor()

# Normalize
normalized = preprocessor.normalize_audio(audio)

# Trim silence
trimmed = preprocessor.trim_silence(audio)

# Pad/truncate to fixed length
processed = preprocessor.preprocess(audio, normalize=True, trim=True, target_duration=10.0)

print(f"Processed audio shape: {processed.shape}")
```

## Feature Extraction

```python
# Extract mel spectrogram
mel_spec = preprocessor.extract_mel_spectrogram(processed)
print(f"Mel spectrogram shape: {mel_spec.shape}")

# Extract MFCC
mfcc = preprocessor.extract_mfcc(processed)
print(f"MFCC shape: {mfcc.shape}")
```

## Visualization

```python
audio_utils = AudioUtils()

# Plot original vs processed
fig, axes = plt.subplots(2,
1, figsize=(12,
8))

# Original
axes[
    0
].plot(audio)
axes[
    0
].set_title("Original Audio")
axes[
    0
].set_xlabel("Samples")
axes[
    0
].set_ylabel("Amplitude")

# Processed
axes[
    1
].plot(processed)
axes[
    1
].set_title("Processed Audio")
axes[
    1
].set_xlabel("Samples")
axes[
    1
].set_ylabel("Amplitude")

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
```
